EQUAL GROUND commends the recommendation sent by the Human Right Commission to the Minister of Justice with regards to repealing and amending Sections 365 and 365A of the Penal Code of Sri Lanka. 

As an organization committed to creating a more equal and inclusive space for members of the LBGTIQ community, we urge the government of Sri Lanka to amend Section 365 and repeal Section 365A of the Penal Code as suggested in the Private Members bill tabled in parliament on 4th April 2023 and thus to;

1. Uphold the Supreme Court Determination on Penal Code (Amendment Bill) published on 9 May 2023;
2. Support the proposed legislative enactment i.e. Private Member's Bill to Amend the Penal Code (Chapter 19) was tabled in Parliament on 4 April 2023;
3. Uphold the rights guaranteed under International Human Rights Instruments, especially the ICCPR

